<script>
(function() {
		var game = new Phaser.Game( 800, 600, Phaser.AUTO, 'game');
    game.state.add('Boot', boot);
    game.state.add('Preloader', preloader);
    game.state.add('MainMenu', mainmenu);
    game.state.add('Game', main);
    game.state.start('Boot');
    })();
</script>
<div id="game"></div>
<div id="readme">
<h2>Sports Kart Dual Dash</h2>
<ul>

<li><strong>High Concept:</strong>
Control two cars and try to get to the end.
</li>

<li><strong>Player Experience Goals:</strong>
Multitasking by controlling two cars and avoiding getting off track.
</li>

<li><strong>Genre:</strong>
Racing Puzzle Maze
</li>

<li><strong>Game play:</strong>
Players use arrow keys and wasd to control two different cars and navigate the track to reach the end. The w and up arrow key accelerates the cars, and the left, right, a, and d keys turn the cars. The s and down keys decelerate. Having one car hit a wall or making it go off screen will make the player lose.
</li>

<li><strong>Prototype goal:</strong>
Create a simple racing puzzle maze game using tilemaps and having the player control two cars.
</li>

<li><strong>Features:</strong>
Simple gameplay, top-down vehicle movement, and one player controlling two cars simultaneously.
</li>

<li><strong>Setting/Premise:</strong>
A race track.
</li>

<li><strong>Story:</strong>
None.
</li>

<li><strong>Target Audience:</strong>
Everyone 10 and up who has interest in sports cars and multitasking.
</li>

<li><strong>Play time:</strong>
2-5 mins.
</li>

<li><strong>Strategies:</strong>
If it's too hard, slow down and maybe even control one car at a time.
</li>

<li><strong>Prototype Assets:</strong>
Tilemap: http://opengameart.org/content/race-track-tiles 
Cars: 
http://opengameart.org/content/car-racer 
Music: 
"Dream Racing" (prozax / http://ocremix.org) 

</li>

<li><strong>Prototype Closest Other Game: Tanks, http://www.gamedevacademy.org/html5-phaser-tutorial-top-down-games-with-tiled/</strong>

</li>

</ul>
</div>
</body>
</html>
